  <bioghist id="aspace_b757503f359358d91f6b7171f78274df">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Beryl Graves (Hodge) is the wife of English poet and author Robert Graves. Their relationship started in 1940 and continued until his death.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_faf8d595c3fc0745c6c56174ad009efa">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Consists of personal records and correspondence pertaining to Laura (Riding) Jackson, collected by Beryl Graves. The correspondence includes letters exchanged between Laura (Riding) Jackson and a variety of corespondents, including Schuyler B. Jackson, publishers Arthur Barker and Constable, and Nancy Cunard. There are also several letters to Robert Graves.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite id="aspace_b71b4bcd4caa8bcdf8ef344713cc055b">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>Beryl Graves collection of Laura (Riding) Jackson correspondence, #6301. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
